        <etym xml:lang="ru">Считая, что %ifs%i восходит, как обычно, к %isp%i, восстанавливаем
                %i*sper-%i || %i*spaira-%i. Такая основа действительно прослеживается в некоторых
                индоевропейских языках со значением ‘острие’, ‘остроконечная палка’, ‘стебель’ и пр.
                Особенно богато представлена в германских языках: <mentioned xml:lang="ang"
                                ><lang/><w>spir</w><gloss><q>длинный
                стебель</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="en"
                                        ><lang/><w>spire</w><gloss><q>шпиль</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
                        xml:lang="en"><w/><gloss><q>горный пик</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned
                        xml:lang="gml"><lang/><w>spīr</w><gloss><q>кончик ростка, побега,
                                        былинки</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="gml"
                                        ><w/><gloss><q>колос</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="gml"><w/><gloss><q>шпиль на башне</q></gloss></mentioned>, ,
                        <mentioned xml:lang="non"
                        ><lang/><w>spira</w><gloss><q>стебель</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="sv"
                        ><lang/><w>spīra</w><gloss><q>стебель</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
                        xml:lang="sv"><w/><gloss><q>отросток</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="sv"><w/><gloss><q>палка</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="sv"><w/><gloss><q>скипетр</q></gloss></mentioned>, . Конечное
                %i-r(а)%i исторически представляет формант; ср. <mentioned xml:lang="sa"
                                ><lang/><w>sphya-</w><gloss><q>щепка</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
                        xml:lang="sa"><w/><gloss><q>палка</q></gloss></mentioned>, (<mentioned
                        xml:lang="ine"><lang/><w>*spei-</w></mentioned>). С формантом %i-n%i мы
                находим этот же корень в <mentioned xml:lang="la"
                                        ><lang/><w>spīna</w><gloss><q>колючка</q></gloss></mentioned>
                и, вероятно, в ос. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_synʒ"/> | %isinʒæ%i ‘колючка’ (из
                %i*fsinʒ-%i ← %i*spin-ti-%i); с формантом %i-k%i в <mentioned xml:lang="la"
                                ><lang/><w>spīca</w><gloss><q>колос</q></gloss></mentioned>.
                Семантическая связь ‘колоса’ с ‘острием’ поддерживается и другими языками; например,
                        <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><lang/><w>στάχυς</w><note type="comment"
                                xml:lang="ru"> (от %i*stegh-%i ‘быть остроконечным’,
                                ‘колоть’)</note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en"> (from
                                %i*stegh-%i ‘be pointed’,
                        ‘prick’)</note><gloss><q>колос</q></gloss></mentioned> , <mentioned
                        xml:lang="got"><lang/><w>ahs</w><gloss><q>колос</q></gloss></mentioned> при
                        <mentioned xml:lang="la"
                        ><lang/><w>acus</w><gloss><q>игла</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="sqj"><lang/><w>ušt</w><gloss><q>колос</q></gloss></mentioned> при
                ос. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_wæxst"/> ‘вертел’; <mentioned xml:lang="ru"
                                ><lang/><w>колос, колоть</w></mentioned>.<note n="1"> PUT NOTE HERE
                </note> Ср. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_sænæfsīr"/>
                                ‘виноград’.%n<bibl><author>Petersson</author><ref target="#ref_LUÅ"
                                /><biblScope xml:lang="ru">1923 XIX %i6%i 4
                                сл.</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">1923 XIX %i6%i 4
                                ff.</biblScope></bibl> — <bibl><ref target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"
                                /><biblScope>60</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
        <etym xml:lang="en">Thinking that %ifs%i usally traces back to %isp%i, we trace the word
                back to %i*sper-%i || %i*spaira-%i. Such a stem can indeed be traced in some
                Indo-European languages with the meaning ‘point’, ‘pointed stick’, ‘stem’, etc. It
                is especially richly represented in Germanic languages: <mentioned xml:lang="ang"
                                ><lang/><w>spir</w><gloss><q>long stem</q></gloss></mentioned>,
                        <mentioned xml:lang="en"><lang/><w>spire</w></mentioned>, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="gml"><lang/><w>spīr</w><gloss><q>tip of sprout, shoot,
                                blade</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="gml"
                                        ><w/><gloss><q>ear</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="gml"><w/><gloss><q>tower spire</q></gloss></mentioned>, ,
                        <mentioned xml:lang="non"
                        ><lang/><w>spira</w><gloss><q>stem</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="sv"
                        ><lang/><w>spīra</w><gloss><q>stem</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
                        xml:lang="sv"><w/><gloss><q>sprout</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="sv"><w/><gloss><q>stick</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="sv"><w/><gloss><q>sceptre</q></gloss></mentioned>, . The final
                %i-r(а)%i is historically a formant; cf. <mentioned xml:lang="sa"
                                ><lang/><w>sphya-</w><gloss><q>chip</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
                        xml:lang="sa"><w/><gloss><q>stick</q></gloss></mentioned>, (<mentioned
                        xml:lang="ine"><lang/><w>*spei-</w></mentioned>). With a formant %i-n%i we
                find the same root in <mentioned xml:lang="la"
                                        ><lang/><w>spīna</w><gloss><q>thorn</q></gloss></mentioned>
                and probably in Ossetic <ref type="xr" target="#entry_synʒ"/> | %isinʒæ%i ‘thorn’
                (from %i*fsinʒ-%i ← %i*spin-ti-%i); with a formant %i-k%i in <mentioned
                        xml:lang="la"><lang/><w>spīca</w><gloss><q>ear</q></gloss></mentioned>. The
                semantic link between ‘ear’ and ‘spike’ is supported by other languages as well;
                e.g., <mentioned xml:lang="grc"><lang/><w>στάχυς</w><note type="comment"
                                xml:lang="ru"> (от %i*stegh-%i ‘быть остроконечным’,
                                ‘колоть’)</note><note type="comment" xml:lang="en"> (from
                                %i*stegh-%i ‘be pointed’,
                        ‘prick’)</note><gloss><q>ear</q></gloss></mentioned> , <mentioned
                        xml:lang="got"><lang/><w>ahs</w><gloss><q>ear</q></gloss></mentioned> with
                        <mentioned xml:lang="la"
                        ><lang/><w>acus</w><gloss><q>needle</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned
                        xml:lang="sqj"><lang/><w>ušt</w><gloss><q>ear</q></gloss></mentioned> with
                Ossetic <ref type="xr" target="#entry_wæxst"/> ‘spit’; <mentioned xml:lang="ru"
                                ><lang/><w>колос</w><gloss><q>ear</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
                        xml:lang="ru"><w>колоть</w><gloss><q>prick</q></gloss></mentioned>, .<note
                        n="1"> PUT NOTE HERE </note> Cf. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_sænæfsīr"/>
                                ‘grapes’.%n<bibl><author>Petersson</author><ref target="#ref_LUÅ"
                                /><biblScope xml:lang="ru">1923 XIX %i6%i 4
                                сл.</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">1923 XIX %i6%i 4
                                ff.</biblScope></bibl> — <bibl><ref target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"
